.TH GAT-DESCRIBE 1 "2026-06-04" "gat 0.3.0" "gat Manual"
.SH NAME
gat-describe \- set or show a worktree description
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gat describe
.I <ticket>
.RI [ text ...]
.RB [ \-\-clear ]
.br
.B gat desc
.I <ticket>
.RI [ text ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
With no text, prints the current description. With trailing words, joins them
into a single description and stores it.
.B \-\-clear
removes the description. The target worktree must exist. Descriptions appear in
.BR gat\-list (1)
and are folded into tmux session names.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-clear
Remove the description.
.TP
.BI \-\-prefix " prefix" ", " \-\-no\-prefix
Ticket prefix handling.
.TP
.BI \-\-format " text|json"
Output format.
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.EX
gat describe 12345 fix the login redirect bug
gat describe 12345
gat describe 12345 \-\-clear
.EE
.RE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR gat (1),
.BR gat\-list (1),
.BR gat\-new (1)
